<node id="&quot;BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee is an insect that can sting as a defensive mechanism, often reacting to perceived threats or disturbances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bee is an organism that reacts to perceived threats and perceives certain actions as aggressive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bee is the primary subject of beekeeping."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bee refers to a social insect known for its complex communication methods, particularly through dance languages."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bee refers to the species of insects that undergo a specific life cycle including egg, larva, and pupa stages."&lt;SEP&gt;"In this context, 'bee' is used metaphorically to describe an insect known for its complex communication methods, particularly through dance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-752a4bcfd49e3f7ebeb351081eb4553f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bd4cd24e118c8cfdf44ccab7c205d81&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ab64a815cd3d2a836336392f2eca48</data>
