<node id="&quot;POLLINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollination is the process by which pollen is transferred from the male parts of a flower to the female parts, enabling plant reproduction and crop production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 76}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CROP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PRODUCT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Crop refers to the honey harvested from the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Crop refers to the plants grown for harvest, which can benefit from bee pollination to ensure adequate yields."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a6fe41559fa35bb0034a3d53d2587c5f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 78}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DISEASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Disease is a condition that affects the health of honey bee colonies, potentially leading to colony weakening or death."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DROUGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drought is a prolonged period of abnormally low rainfall, which can stress honey bee colonies and affect their survival."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HARSH WINTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A harsh winter is a severe cold season that can negatively impact honey bee colonies, particularly in northern regions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREDATORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Predators are animals that pose a threat to honey bee colonies, such as bears or birds, which can attack and harm the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NORTH AMERICA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"North America is a continent where honey bee colonies face various challenges, including disease, drought, and harsh winters."&lt;SEP&gt;"North America is a region where honey bee colonies struggle to survive, particularly in the northern regions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e4d27c8d8b004a26dce6446ca790153</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 76}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A colony refers to a group of honey bees living together, managed by a queen bee and maintained by worker bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony is the living space and social structure of the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony refers to the group of bees living together in the hive, working collectively to maintain and expand the hive structure."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony refers to the group of bees living together in the hive.""&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony refers to the group of bees working together, led by the queen, to maintain and grow the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Colony is the group of bees living together in the hive, including the queen, drones, and workers."&lt;SEP&gt;"The colony is a group of bees living in a hive and is currently less dependent on feed but still vulnerable to robbery."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bf1cda15c3e18b5b766dda26758bb950&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1c25c7431109863bb945279517ed9aab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-815f215becbebf90c088cce626290fc0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FERAL COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feral Colonies refer to wild honey bee colonies that exist independently and are subject to regular deaths and replacements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feral colonies are wild honey bee colonies that live independently without human management."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e4d27c8d8b004a26dce6446ca790153</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey bees are the species Apis mellifera, known for their role in pollination and honey production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4957ec7ee118ac56c14f04d82744a8e6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Bee is the reproductive female in a bee colony, responsible for laying eggs and maintaining the genetic diversity of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen bees are the reproductive females in a honey bee colony, responsible for laying eggs."</data>
