<node id="&quot;BANKRUPTCY COURT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bankruptcy Court is a judicial body responsible for overseeing bankruptcy cases and making rulings on claims and transfers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is a judicial body that may issue orders limiting transfers of claims."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is a judicial body with jurisdiction over bankruptcy cases, mentioned in the context of legal or structural impediments."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is a legal entity that requires permission for certain actions, specifically related to changes or withdrawals of votes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is an entity responsible for overseeing the restructuring process and approving Milestones."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is the entity whose calendar affects the negotiations and extensions of milestones."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is the judicial body that can appoint trustees, receivers, or examiners to operate and manage the Company’s businesses."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is the judicial body that needs to approve the treatment of the Expense Reimbursement Amount as administrative expenses."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is the judicial body where motions and objections are filed and decided upon."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is the judicial body where the Company intends to file various motions and pleadings."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Bankruptcy Court is the judicial body where certain motions and pleadings are filed during a restructuring process."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e243a6e605d9bda590d41e79f0bdcf6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1048bb352f0f09318b7c1004aeb9e1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a084f2e9cb7d42ed40a5f082d5224a62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19f1f2ac97e350d7978ba6d7f910d3d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a98abc7661191612db1330d484a309bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a6fe41559fa35bb0034a3d53d2587c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e4d27c8d8b004a26dce6446ca790153&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-497066cb85846685befbf13ad5fbcafa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f645c16a1cbf2169e4377767b2bca09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07a778754579048a8dc70de19952fd25&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-601adfca36708dd405154d57329e95d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 25}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUPPORTING LENDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Supporting Lender is a party involved in the Prepetition Credit Agreement and Prepetition Facility Agreements, with rights to transfer claims."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supporting Lender is a party to an agreement, with rights and obligations related to the termination and releases in the Plan."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supporting Lender is an entity that holds Prepetition Agreement Claims and is involved in transfers and agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supporting Lender is an organization that has agreed to support the plan and may change or withdraw its vote or release as per the agreement terms."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supporting Lender is an organization that supports the Plan and may need to change or withdraw its vote, requiring Bankruptcy Court permission."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supporting Lender is an organization whose Prepetition Agreement Claim is subject to transfer and is bound by the representations and warranties set forth in the Agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e243a6e605d9bda590d41e79f0bdcf6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1048bb352f0f09318b7c1004aeb9e1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5417895366679d5abd3d326e6c67df2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e4d27c8d8b004a26dce6446ca790153&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07a778754579048a8dc70de19952fd25&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-601adfca36708dd405154d57329e95d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 71}, {"level": 3, "cluster": 93}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRANSFEREE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Transferee is a party that agrees to be bound by the terms of the agreement after receiving transferred Prepetition Agreement Claims."&lt;SEP&gt;"Transferee is an entity that agrees to be bound by the terms of the agreement after receiving transferred Prepetition Agreement Claims."&lt;SEP&gt;"Transferee is an entity that may acquire or assume Prepetition Agreement Claims from a Supporting Lender."&lt;SEP&gt;"Transferee is an organization that holds Prepetition Agreement Claims and is deemed to make representations and warranties upon consummation of a Transfer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e243a6e605d9bda590d41e79f0bdcf6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e4d27c8d8b004a26dce6446ca790153&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5417895366679d5abd3d326e6c67df2</data>
