<node id="&quot;AGREEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Agreement is a contract between parties, likely involving Supporting Lenders and possibly other entities, with terms related to releases and exculpations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Agreement is a legal document that outlines the terms and conditions of the Restructuring process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Agreement is the document that outlines the terms and conditions agreed upon by the Supporting Lenders and the Company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Agreement is the main contract between the Company, Debtors, and Supporting Lenders, outlining the terms and conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Agreement is the main contract or document that outlines the terms and conditions between the parties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Agreement refers to a legal contract between parties, specifically mentioning the Expense Reimbursement Amount and the Supporting Lenders."&lt;SEP&gt;"The agreement is the main document that outlines the terms and conditions between the Supporting Lenders and the Debtors."</data>
