  <data key="d1">"Commercial operators are beekeepers who run a full-scale commercial operation, focusing primarily on income from beekeeping."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-90bb6316aa4aebbba7c436b6735776e9</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AGRICULTURAL COMPONENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Agricultural component refers to the advancements and developments in agriculture, particularly in beekeeping and apiculture."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-90bb6316aa4aebbba7c436b6735776e9</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 50}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMPROVED BEEKEEPING PRACTICES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Improved beekeeping practices are the result of research and education, enhancing the efficiency and effectiveness of beekeeping."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-90bb6316aa4aebbba7c436b6735776e9</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 50}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ATTITUDES AND LIFESTYLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Attitudes and lifestyles changed due to the Industrial Revolution, impacting how people viewed and engaged in beekeeping."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-90bb6316aa4aebbba7c436b6735776e9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EVOLUTION OF BEEKEEPER TYPES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The evolution of beekeeper types from hobbyists to commercial operators occurred as a result of advancements in beekeeping and changes in societal attitudes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-90bb6316aa4aebbba7c436b6735776e9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FULL-TIME EMPLOYMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Full-time employment is the primary occupation of individuals who do not engage in beekeeping as a sideline or hobby."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-90bb6316aa4aebbba7c436b6735776e9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INFORMAL CLASSIFICATION OF BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An informal classification of beekeepers exists, recognizing three main types: hobbyists, sideliners, and commercial operators."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-90bb6316aa4aebbba7c436b6735776e9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SIDELINE OPERATOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A sideline operator is someone who keeps bees as a small sideline business, typically with fewer than 200 hives, and uses it as supplementary income to other full-time employment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMMERCIAL BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A commercial beekeeper is someone who makes their entire income from bees, often through honey production, crop pollination, queen or package production, and owns anywhere from a few hundred to several thousand hives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPING INDUSTRY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The beekeeping industry includes various components such as honey producers, pollinators, queen and package producers, manufacturers and distributors of beekeeping equipment, research and educational facilities, and publishers of beekeeping materials."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CANCER CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cancer cells are abnormal cells that grow uncontrollably and can spread to other parts of the body, posing a serious health threat."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CANCER RESEARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cancer research involves efforts to develop more effective and safer therapies tailored to individual patients, addressing the limitations of current treatments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hives refer to the structures where bees live and produce honey, which are managed by both sideline operators and commercial beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEDERAL, STATE, AND ACADEMIC RESEARCH AND EDUCATIONAL FACILITIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"These facilities conduct research and provide education in beekeeping, impacting the industry."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PUBLISHERS OF BEEKEEPING MAGAZINES, JOURNALS, AND BOOKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Publishers produce materials that educate and inform beekeepers about best practices and new developments in the field."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MANUFACTURERS AND DISTRIBUTORS OF BEEKEEPING EQUIPMENT AND SUPPLIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"These organizations produce and distribute tools and materials needed for beekeeping, supporting the industry."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey production is a specific activity within the beekeeping industry, involving the collection and processing of honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ee2dcad4dcf8ac0aace4c216b243d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CROP POLLINATION&quot;">
