</node>
<node id="&quot;JANET ROWLEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Janet Rowley is a researcher who discovered a specific mutation that led to the development of Gleevec."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CIBA-GEIGY PHARMACEUTICAL COMPANY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Ciba-Geigy is a pharmaceutical company based in Basel, Switzerland, where Nick Lydon and Alex Matter worked on developing cancer therapies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NICK LYDON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nick Lydon is a scientist at Ciba-Geigy who contributed to the development of Gleevec."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALEX MATTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Alex Matter is a scientist at Ciba-Geigy who contributed to the development of Gleevec."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENDO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Endo is mentioned as a scientist who used traditional trial and error methods in drug development."&lt;SEP&gt;"Endo is mentioned as someone who searched through nature for inhibitors, contrasting with the rational design approach used in the research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BASEL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Basel is a city in Switzerland where Ciba-Geigy is located."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CML&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"CML is a type of cancer that involves uncontrolled cell multiplication due to the _bcr_ / _abl_ translocation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;_BCR_ / _ABL_ TRANSLOCATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"_bcr_ / _abl_ translocation is a genetic mutation that causes hyperactive protein kinase, leading to uncontrolled cell multiplication in CML."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;_RB_ REPRESSOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"_Rb_ repressor is a protein that normally inhibits cell division, but is inactivated by the _bcr_ / _abl_ translocation in CML."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HYPERACTIVE PROTEIN KINASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hyperactive protein kinase is caused by the _bcr_ / _abl_ translocation and leads to uncontrolled cell multiplication in CML."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNCONTROLLED CELL MULTIPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Uncontrolled cell multiplication is a result of the _bcr_ / _abl_ translocation and is characteristic of CML."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TIRELESS IN ENCOURAGING DRUG DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A physician who was tireless in encouraging drug development played a crucial role in the success of Gleevec and statins."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRUG DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drug development is the process of creating new medications, including Gleevec and statins."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPECTACULAR CLINICAL SUCCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Spectacular clinical success refers to the successful outcomes of the drug development efforts, such as the success of Gleevec."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICAL HISTORY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Medical history encompasses the significant events and developments in medicine, such as the success of Gleevec."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRIAL AND ERROR METHODS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Trial and error methods are traditional approaches used in drug development, contrasting with the innovative methods used by Ciba-Geigy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHARMACEUTICAL INDUSTRY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pharmaceutical industry refers to the sector involved in the development and production of drugs, exemplified by Ciba-Geigy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Pharmaceutical Industry is referenced as using traditional trial and error methods, contrasting with the rational design approach used in the research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-94340091b0068ef391cdac4899a68bc1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWITZERLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Switzerland is the country where the research is taking place, known for its contributions to scientific advancements in oncology."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RATIONAL DESIGN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rational Design is the method used to devise molecules that fit into and block the active site of kinases, aiming to inhibit cancer cell growth."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;C-ABL KINASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"c-abl Kinase is a specific kinase targeted by the inhibitor compounds developed in the research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CML CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"CML Cells are cancer cells associated with Chronic Myeloid Leukemia, which are targeted by the inhibitor compounds."&lt;SEP&gt;"CML cells refer to Chronic Myeloid Leukemia cells, which were used in the initial laboratory testing of the drug."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BRIAN DRUKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brian Druker is a physician at Oregon Health Sciences University in Portland who tested the compounds on CML cells and found promising results."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OREGON HEALTH SCIENCES UNIVERSITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Oregon Health Sciences University is the institution where Brian Druker works and conducts research on CML cells."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CIBA-GEIGY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Ciba-Geigy is the company conducting the research and developing the inhibitor compounds."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ciba-Geigy was a pharmaceutical company that merged with Sandoz to form Novartis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SANDOZ PHARMACEUTICAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sandoz Pharmaceutical is another company involved in the merger with Ciba-Geigy, continuing the development of the CML-specific drug."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LYDON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lydon is a researcher involved in the development of the inhibitor compounds and provided them to Brian Druker for testing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Lydon was a key figure at Novartis who resigned after the drug's safety concerns were raised."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Matter is a journalist who reported on the development and challenges of the drug."&lt;SEP&gt;"Matter is a researcher involved in the development of the inhibitor compounds and worked with Lydon and Druker."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIRST TESTING IN ANIMALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The first testing in animals is a crucial step in advancing the inhibitor compounds from initial development to clinical trials."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOXICOLOGY TESTS IN DOGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Toxicology Tests in Dogs are conducted to ensure the safety of the inhibitor compounds before human trials."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTRAVENOUS USE IN HUMANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Intravenous Use in Humans is a method of administration that was initially considered but later found to be unsafe based on the toxicology tests."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MERGER OF CIBA-GEIGY AND SANDOZ PHARMACEUTICAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The merger of Ciba-Geigy and Sandoz Pharmaceutical is a significant corporate event that continues the development of the CML-specific drug."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b9dbcad0721ad088ca30cce5b4340340</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SANDOZ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sandoz was a pharmaceutical company that merged with Ciba-Geigy to form Novartis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NOVARTIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Novartis is the result of the merger between Ciba-Geigy and Sandoz, and it continued the development of the drug."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRUKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Druker is a physician who started administering a drug to CML patients in a laboratory setting, monitoring both their disease and potential side effects."&lt;SEP&gt;"Druker is a physician who was instrumental in the development and testing of the drug, advocating for its use despite safety concerns."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANIEL VASELLA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Daniel Vasella is the new CEO of Novartis who supported the clinical trial of the drug in humans."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CML PATIENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"CML patients are the subjects of a drug trial conducted by Druker and other physicians, specifically for Chronic Myeloid Leukemia."&lt;SEP&gt;"CML patients are the target patient group for the drug, suffering from Chronic Myeloid Leukemia."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOXICOLOGIST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A person who provided expert opinion on the drug's safety."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WHITE CELL COUNT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"White cell count is a medical measurement used to assess the health of CML patients, with normal levels ranging from 4,000–10,000 cells per microliter of blood and elevated levels in CML patients reaching 100,000–500,000 cells per microliter."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC 'BRAKES'&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic 'brakes' refer to mechanisms within cells that prevent uncontrolled growth, such as tumor suppressors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RETINOBLASTOMA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Retinoblastoma is a genetic disorder that typically affects children at an early age and can run in families, characterized by the deletion of a portion of both copies of chromosome 13, suggesting the loss of a tumor suppressor gene is key to its development."&lt;SEP&gt;"Retinoblastoma is a rare cancer of the eye that often develops in children and sometimes runs in families, providing a genetic clue to the understanding of cancer mechanisms."&lt;SEP&gt;"Retinoblastoma is a type of cancer that affects the retina of the eye, often linked to Rb gene mutations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHROMOSOME 13&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chromosome 13 is a specific part of the human genome where deletions can occur, leading to the development of retinoblastoma."&lt;SEP&gt;"Chromosome 13 is mentioned as the site of genetic deletions in retinoblastoma cases, highlighting its importance in the genetic basis of the disease."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHYSICIANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Physicians, including Druker, are conducting the drug trial on CML patients, indicating their role in the research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRUG&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The drug being administered to CML patients is part of a clinical trial aimed at managing the disease."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACCELERATOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An accelerator metaphorically represents the uncontrolled growth of cancer cells, similar to a car's accelerator being stuck."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BRAKE LINES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brake lines represent the genetic mechanisms that prevent uncontrolled cell growth, analogous to the braking system in a car."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUMOR SUPPRESSORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tumor suppressors are genetic mechanisms that help prevent uncontrolled cell growth, acting as brakes on cancer development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC DELETIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic deletions, such as those observed in retinoblastoma, are events that can lead to the loss of tumor suppressors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNCONTROLLED GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Uncontrolled growth is a key characteristic of cancer, driven by the loss of genetic 'brakes'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Oncogenes are genes that can cause cancer when mutated, often requiring the alteration of just one copy of the gene to exert their effects."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROTO-ONCOGENE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Proto-oncogenes are normal genes that can become oncogenes when mutated, typically requiring only one copy to be altered for cancer formation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUMOR SUPPRESSOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tumor suppressors are genes that normally prevent or suppress tumor formation, and their loss or alteration can lead to cancer, exemplified by the retinoblastoma gene."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RB GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GENE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Rb gene, also known as the retinoblastoma gene, is a tumor suppressor gene whose function is to control cell division and prevent tumor formation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DNA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"DNA is the genetic material that carries the instructions used in the development and functioning of all known living organisms and contains the hereditary information passed on from parents to offspring."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CELL CYCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The cell cycle is the series of events that takes place in a cell leading to its division and duplication, including the replication of DNA and the division of the cell into two daughter cells."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CELL DIVISION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cell division is the process by which a parent cell divides into two or more daughter cells, which is a fundamental aspect of growth, development, and repair in multicellular organisms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;_BCR_ / _ABL_&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GENE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The _bcr_ / _abl_ gene is an oncogene that, when mutated, can lead to the formation of chronic myeloid leukemia (CML), where the alteration of one copy of the gene is sufficient to cause cancer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CANCER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cancer is a disease characterized by uncontrolled cell growth due to the inactivation of the Rb repressor gene."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cancer is a group of diseases characterized by the uncontrolled growth and spread of abnormal cells, which can originate from various types of tissues and organs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RB PROTEIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rb protein is a tumor suppressor that controls a critical decision in the cell life cycle by blocking DNA replication."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CELL MULTIPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cell multiplication refers to the process of cell division and growth, which is regulated by the Rb gene."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cell multiplication refers to the process of cells copying their DNA and dividing into two, which is highly regulated."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DNA REPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"DNA replication is the process where cells duplicate their genetic material before division."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OSTEOSARCOMA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Osteosarcoma is a type of bone cancer that can be associated with Rb mutations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LUNG CANCER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lung cancer is a type of cancer that affects the lungs and can also be associated with Rb mutations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROTEIN KINASES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Protein kinases are enzymes that add phosphate groups to proteins, regulating their activity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BCR/ABL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GENE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"bcr/abl is an oncogene protein that increases the phosphorylation of Rb, inhibiting its activity and promoting continuous cell multiplication."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEGATIVE REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Negative regulation refers to mechanisms that inhibit or reduce a biological process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Negative regulation refers to the inhibition of a process, such as the production of an enzyme, by an intermediary factor."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22254c52213838b97f2638a84916771e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DOUBLE-NEGATIVE REGULATORY LOGIC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Double-negative regulatory logic applies to the regulation of Rb protein activity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Double-negative regulatory logic involves two layers of inhibition or activation in a biological pathway."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ONCOGENE PROTEINS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Oncogene proteins are genes that can cause cancer when mutated or expressed at high levels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOSS OR ALTERATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Loss or alteration of the Rb protein can lead to uncontrolled cell multiplication."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STUDIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Extensive studies have revealed the functions of the Rb protein."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUMOR SUPPRESSOR GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Rb protein is a tumor suppressor gene."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNCONTROLLED WAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"When Rb is inactivated, cells continue to multiply in an uncontrolled way."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHOSPHORYLATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Phosphorylation of Rb protein by protein kinases can inactivate it."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTINUOUS CELL MULTIPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Continuous cell multiplication results from the inactivation of Rb."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC MATERIAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic material that cells duplicate during DNA replication."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REPRESSOR OF CELL MULTIPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rb protein acts as a repressor of cell multiplication."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MAJOR EARLY CHECKPOINT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rb acts at a major early checkpoint in the cell cycle by blocking DNA replication."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c16eda8ad4f7a656049e25ddcd139d13</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rb is a gene that acts as a repressor of cell multiplication, and its inactivation or loss allows for constitutive growth, playing a crucial role in cancer development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MONOD AND JACOB'S SPECULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Monod and Jacob's speculation refers to their hypothesis that cancer results from the inactivation of a repressor of cell multiplication, which aligns with the role of the Rb gene."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOGICAL THERAPY AND RATIONAL DRUGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Logical therapy and rational drugs refer to targeted approaches to treat cancer by addressing the specific genetic mutations that disrupt cell growth regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SURGERY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Surgery is a method used to treat cancer, often involving the removal of tumors or affected tissues."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IRRADIATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Irradiation is another method used to treat cancer, involving the use of high-energy radiation to kill cancer cells."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COCKTAILS OF DRUGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cocktails of drugs are a combination of medications used to treat cancer, targeting dividing cells."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEBTORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Debtors are entities that owe money to the Company, but no specific details are provided about them."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors are the parties in the bankruptcy case who owe the Expense Reimbursement Amount and acknowledge the terms of the Agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors are the parties involved in the bankruptcy proceedings and subject to the requirements outlined in the agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors are the parties to whom the Company owes money or has obligations, and their knowledge is considered in assessing compliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors are the parties who owe money or are subject to the terms of the agreement mentioned in the text."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the entities involved in bankruptcy proceedings, specifically the Company in this context."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the entities involved in the bankruptcy cases and are required to provide documents and file objections as per the agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the parties involved in the agreement who are required to pay the Expense Reimbursement Amount upon termination of the agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the parties involved in the agreement, whose material assets are subject to certain conditions without the consent of the DIP Agent."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the parties who owe money or have obligations to the company mentioned in the text."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refers to the parties involved in a financial agreement, likely the entities seeking restructuring."</data>
