  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Flower is a plant part where bees can sip nectar, and it can be perceived as a threat by a bee if the bee feels its territory is invaded."&lt;SEP&gt;"Flower is a plant part where bees often feed on nectar and perceive human proximity as an attack."&lt;SEP&gt;"Flower is a visible trait mentioned in the text, which could be influenced by enzyme regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b75be069c2e11b99b8211d14f57d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ab64a815cd3d2a836336392f2eca48</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 36}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar is a sweet liquid produced by flowers that bees collect to make honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is a sweet liquid produced by plants that attracts bees and can be perceived as a threat if bees feel their territory is invaded."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is a sweet liquid produced by plants that bees collect to make honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-409158f771708f639ac427a52dff0ac0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78ab64a815cd3d2a836336392f2eca48</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 36}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ATTACK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Attack is a perceived threat or aggression that can trigger a defensive reaction in a bee."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-78ab64a815cd3d2a836336392f2eca48</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 36}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Home is the protected area around a bee's nest where it defends against perceived threats."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-78ab64a815cd3d2a836336392f2eca48</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 36}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VANDALISM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vandalism is an action that can provoke bees to become more reactive due to perceived harassment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANIMAL DEPREDATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Animal depredation is another form of harassment that can make bees more reactive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWATTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swatting is a clear aggressive action that can trigger a defensive reaction in bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BODY CHEMISTRY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Body chemistry can affect how bees react to humans, either provoking or calming them."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRAGRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fragrances such as perfume, deodorant, or hair dressing can attract or repel bees based on their scent."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HUMAN PROXIMITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Human proximity can be perceived as a threat by bees, especially if it is sudden or aggressive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEFENSIVE REACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Defensive reaction is a behavior exhibited by bees in response to perceived threats."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERCEIVED AGGRESSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Perceived aggression is any action or presence that triggers a defensive response in bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BENIGN INTENTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Benign intentions refer to actions that are not meant to harm but can still trigger a defensive reaction in bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERSISTENT ANNOYANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Persistent annoyance is a repeated action that can make bees more reactive over time."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICAL ADVICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Medical advice can lead some people to believe they are allergic to bee stings, even if they are not."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWELLING AND PAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swelling and pain are physical reactions that can occur after a bee sting, even if the person is not truly allergic."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-35887a077ff8cc664c022e0850b536e3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE STINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee stings are incidents where bees inject venom into humans, causing various reactions ranging from mild to severe."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHYSICIAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A physician is a medical doctor who may diagnose and advise patients about potential allergies to bee stings."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWELLING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swelling is a physical reaction that can occur after a bee sting, varying in severity and duration."&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Swelling is a physical reaction that may occur after a sting, ranging from mild to severe and persistent for a day or two."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5921f5fba3b5629fc6de48f8112eb52</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ITCHING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Itching is a sensation that can persist at the site of a bee sting, sometimes lasting for several hours."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SYSTEMIC REACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Systemic reaction is a more severe response to a bee sting, involving the entire body and potentially life-threatening symptoms."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MILD REACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mild reaction is a less severe response to a bee sting, characterized by localized pain and swelling."&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Mild reaction is a less severe response to a bee stings, characterized by localized pain and swelling."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEVERE REACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Severe reaction is a more intense response to a bee sting, often involving significant swelling and other systemic symptoms."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALLERGY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Allergy is a condition where the immune system reacts abnormally to substances like bee venom, potentially causing severe reactions."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESISTANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Resistance is the body's ability to build tolerance to the effects of repeated bee stings, often resulting in milder reactions over time."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WELT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Welt is a raised, red area of skin that forms at the site of a bee sting, often accompanied by pain and itching."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pain is a sensation that can occur at the site of a bee sting, typically lasting for a minute or so."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNPLEASANTNESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Unpleasantness is a subjective feeling of discomfort or distress that can accompany certain reactions to bee stings."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FUZZINESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fuzziness refers to the unclear distinction between local and systemic reactions to bee stings."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CAUTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Caution is the practice of being careful and taking precautions to avoid severe reactions to bee stings."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LINE BETWEEN LOCAL AND SYSTEMIC REACTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The line between local and systemic reactions is the boundary that separates mild from severe responses to bee stings."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOCAL REACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Local reaction is a mild response to a bee sting, typically limited to the sting site and including pain, swelling, and itching."&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01dc47474e72c6cb5f3078a19a6a5b3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALLERGIC REACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Allergic reaction is a term that is not properly used to describe the described swelling, as it is not life-threatening and does not fit the typical definition of an allergic reaction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f5921f5fba3b5629fc6de48f8112eb52</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANAPHYLACTIC SHOCK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Anaphylactic shock is a life-threatening condition that can occur after a sting, characterized by symptoms such as nausea, body rash, difficulty in breathing, and dizziness."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f5921f5fba3b5629fc6de48f8112eb52</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STING KIT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sting kit is a medical device prescribed by a physician to treat severe allergic reactions to stings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f5921f5fba3b5629fc6de48f8112eb52</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOLERANCE TO STINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tolerance to stings is the ability to withstand multiple stings without severe reactions, often developed by regular exposure."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f5921f5fba3b5629fc6de48f8112eb52</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARVAL STAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larval stage is a developmental stage in the lifecycle of a bee, where the larva develops before pupation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f5921f5fba3b5629fc6de48f8112eb52</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PUPAL STAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pupal stage is a developmental stage in the lifecycle of a bee, where the pupa transforms into an adult bee."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f5921f5fba3b5629fc6de48f8112eb52</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADULT BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adult bee is the fully developed form of a bee, capable of performing various tasks within the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adult bee is the fully developed form of the worker bee after emerging from the pupal stage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f5921f5fba3b5629fc6de48f8112eb52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONE BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drone Bee is a male bee whose primary role is to mate with the queen bee."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 82}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NURSE BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nurse Bee is a worker bee that feeds the larvae with royal jelly and brood food."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CELL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cell is a hexagonal chamber in the comb where bees develop and store food."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cell is a structure within the hive where the queen lays eggs and where larvae develop into adults."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cell is the basic unit of life, where metabolic processes and gene expression take place."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a1fe5c5c561e507d8c235678840d518&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 82}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROYAL JELLY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Royal Jelly is a secretion from the heads of nurse bees used to feed the queen and developing larvae."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood Food is a mixture of glandular secretions, honey, and pollen used to feed developing larvae."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPERMATHECA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Spermatheca is an organ in the queen bee's body that stores sperm received during mating."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARVA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larva is the developing stage of a bee after hatching from an egg, before entering the pupal stage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Larva is the stage in the bee's life cycle where the egg hatches and the insect develops before forming a cocoon."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PUPA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pupa is the stage in the bee's life cycle where the larva transforms into an adult bee inside the cocoon."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pupa is the stage of development in which the worker bee matures inside the cocoon."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdc88706dd1714ba88517a6b8ca4e980&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COCOON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cocoon is a protective structure spun by the developing worker bee during the pupal stage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD PERIOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood period is the developmental stage from egg through emergence, taking place within a waxen cell in the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOUSE BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"House bee is a worker bee that performs tasks within the hive for the first half of its adult life, typically 2 to 3 weeks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 57}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIELD BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Field bee is a worker bee that performs foraging tasks outside the hive for the second half of its adult life, typically about 2 weeks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 57}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Worker is a female bee that performs all tasks necessary to the success of the colony except reproduction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 81}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollen is a fine powder produced by plants that bees collect to feed the brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 81}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPOLIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Propolis is a resinous material collected by bees from trees and used to seal gaps in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 81}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Water is a resource collected by bees for various purposes, including cooling the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 81}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FLOWERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Flowers are the source of nectar and pollen collected by worker bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Comb is a structure built by bees using wax, used for storing honey and raising brood.""&lt;SEP&gt;"Comb is the hexagonal structure built by bees using wax, used for storing honey, pollen, and raising larvae."&lt;SEP&gt;"Comb is the structure built by bees to store food and house the brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bf1cda15c3e18b5b766dda26758bb950&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1073b6d62431432ec578fe2bf1d1f663</data>
