<node id="&quot;MONOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Monod is a scientist who discovered the concept of allosteric regulation and its importance in protein activity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist who makes a breakthrough in understanding repression and feedback inhibition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist who needed a fresh approach to discover the repressor and understand enzyme regulation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist who was researching the regulation of enzyme production in bacteria."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist who, along with his collaborators, discovered the mechanism of enzyme regulation involving lactose and a repressor protein."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b75be069c2e11b99b8211d14f57d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-babaf934dcb765f08d028d1b33488eef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95d378a4a5d837b5df62cf1349844f34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a1fe5c5c561e507d8c235678840d518</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 40}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 74}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REPRESSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Repression is a phenomenon in molecular biology where gene expression is turned off."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3a1fe5c5c561e507d8c235678840d518</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 40}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 74}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDBACK INHIBITION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feedback Inhibition is a regulatory mechanism in metabolic pathways where the end product inhibits an earlier step."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feedback Inhibition is a regulatory mechanism where the end product of a metabolic pathway inhibits an earlier step in the pathway, often through allosteric regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-95d378a4a5d837b5df62cf1349844f34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a1fe5c5c561e507d8c235678840d518</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 40}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 73}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENZYME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Enzyme is a biological catalyst produced by bacteria in response to the presence of lactose, which helps in breaking down lactose into simpler molecules."&lt;SEP&gt;"Enzyme is a biological catalyst that speeds up chemical reactions, often regulated through allosteric mechanisms."&lt;SEP&gt;"Enzyme is a protein that catalyzes biochemical reactions, specifically mentioned in the context of fitting substrates into an active site."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-95d378a4a5d837b5df62cf1349844f34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a1fe5c5c561e507d8c235678840d518&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUBSTRATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Substrate is a molecule acted upon by an enzyme, such as sugars or amino acids."&lt;SEP&gt;"Substrate is the molecule that binds to the active site of an enzyme and undergoes a chemical reaction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-95d378a4a5d837b5df62cf1349844f34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a1fe5c5c561e507d8c235678840d518</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THREONINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Threonine is a specific substrate that fits into the active site of the enzyme Monod was studying."&lt;SEP&gt;"Threonine is an amino acid that fits into the active pocket of the enzyme, serving as a reference point for understanding enzyme binding."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-95d378a4a5d837b5df62cf1349844f34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a1fe5c5c561e507d8c235678840d518</data>
