<node id="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Container holding the queen cage and feeder can."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package is a method of acquiring a queen bee, often used when starting a new colony or replacing a lost queen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package refers to a queen cage containing a queen bee and worker bees, used for transportation and replacement purposes in beekeeping."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package refers to the container holding bees, feed, and a queen cage for installation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package refers to the container holding the queen cage and feeder can, which needs to be opened for inspection."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-815f215becbebf90c088cce626290fc0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-409158f771708f639ac427a52dff0ac0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9adb318b0497cb51bfeea12fbe24d4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4807ea62df150b7fa65c431a05d04369</data>
