</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN CAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Cage is a container used to transport a queen bee and a few worker bees, often used in beekeeping to ensure the survival of the colony during transportation or replacement of the queen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen cage is a container used to house a queen bee during the process of moving or splitting a beehive.""&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen cage is a container used to transport a queen bee, suspended by a metal disk, and often accompanied by worker bees who serve as attendants."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen cage is a container within the package that holds the queen bee and is used to protect her during transportation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bf1cda15c3e18b5b766dda26758bb950&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-409158f771708f639ac427a52dff0ac0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9adb318b0497cb51bfeea12fbe24d4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4807ea62df150b7fa65c431a05d04369</data>
