<node id="&quot;LACTOSE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lactose is a food source that triggers the production of enzymes in bacteria, allowing them to break it down into simpler molecules."&lt;SEP&gt;"Lactose is a sugar molecule that, when present, triggers the production of an enzyme necessary for its breakdown."&lt;SEP&gt;"Lactose is a sugar that plays a crucial role in regulating enzyme synthesis by affecting the repressor protein."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22254c52213838b97f2638a84916771e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-babaf934dcb765f08d028d1b33488eef</data>
