<node id="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A repressor is a protein that prevents the transcription of a gene, thus inhibiting the production of an enzyme when lactose is absent."&lt;SEP&gt;"Repressor is a term used to describe a molecule that inhibits another molecule, in this context, it is part of the regulation of enzyme activity."&lt;SEP&gt;"The repressor is a protein that specifically represses the synthesis of the β-galactosidase enzyme."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b75be069c2e11b99b8211d14f57d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22254c52213838b97f2638a84916771e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-babaf934dcb765f08d028d1b33488eef</data>
