<node id="&quot;ENZYME REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Enzyme Regulation refers to the mechanisms by which enzymes are controlled, including the role of repressors."&lt;SEP&gt;"Enzyme regulation is a biological mechanism involving the control of enzyme production based on the presence or absence of specific molecules, such as lactose."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-32b75be069c2e11b99b8211d14f57d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22254c52213838b97f2638a84916771e</data>
