<node id="&quot;PREPETITION FACILITY AGREEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Prepetition Facility Agreement is another pre-existing agreement that is referenced in the agreement and includes terms for fees and expenses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09b10f93e9533caaeadef2357fac4779</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 62}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIP ORDERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"DIP Orders are court orders granting the use of cash collateral or adequate protection to the Prepetition Lenders during the restructuring process."&lt;SEP&gt;"DIP Orders are court orders that govern the use of debtor-in-possession financing during the bankruptcy proceedings."&lt;SEP&gt;"DIP Orders refer to the orders granting protection to the Prepetition Lenders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-19f1f2ac97e350d7978ba6d7f910d3d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52108fe481d472cc1ff728e87732c8fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09b10f93e9533caaeadef2357fac4779</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGE SITE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Forage site is the location where bees find food, communicated through the dance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-752a4bcfd49e3f7ebeb351081eb4553f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CROSSWIND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Crosswind is a wind blowing across the intended flight path of the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Crosswind is a wind blowing at an angle to the direction of travel, affecting the flight path of the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-752a4bcfd49e3f7ebeb351081eb4553f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OBSTRUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Obstruction is an obstacle that requires a detour, which bees indicate through their dance language."&lt;SEP&gt;"Obstruction is an obstacle that the bees must navigate around or over."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-752a4bcfd49e3f7ebeb351081eb4553f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANCER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dancer refers to a bee that performs the dance to communicate information to other bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-752a4bcfd49e3f7ebeb351081eb4553f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTAMINATED OR POISONOUS FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Contaminated or poisonous food is a threat to the hive, triggering a specific dance to alert the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALARM DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Alarm dance is a specific type of dance performed by bees to indicate the presence of contaminated or poisonous food in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOUSE BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"House bees are worker bees that perform various tasks within the hive, including cleaning and grooming."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIELD BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Field bees are worker bees that gather nectar and pollen outside the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SICKLE OR CRESCENT DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sickle or crescent dance is a type of dance that serves as a transition between the round and wag-tail dances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLEANING DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cleaning dance is a solicitation by the dancer to other nearby bees to clean and groom her."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANCE LANGUAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dance language is a form of communication used by bees to convey information about food sources and other important details."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STRAIGHT LINE DISTANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Straight Line Distance is the shortest distance between two points, which bees use to indicate the direction and distance to a food source."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCOUTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Scouting is the process of searching for food sources, which bees engage in when the dance language is not available."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TIMELY BASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Timely Basis refers to the quick gathering and dissemination of information, reducing the time spent on scouting."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 79}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPARATIVE QUALITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Comparative Quality is the information provided by the dance language on the relative quality of different food sources."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESOURCE EXPLOITATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Resource Exploitation is the full utilization of the neighborhood's resources by the bees using the dance language."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INFORMATION DISSEMINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Information Dissemination is the quick spread of information among bees through the dance language."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 79}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RANDOM SCOUTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Random Scouting is the process of searching for food sources when the dance language is not available."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONY SUCCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Colony Success is the overall success of the bee colony, which depends on the effectiveness of the dance language."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TIMELY SCOUTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Timely Scouting is the reduction in time spent on scouting due to the quick information provided by the dance language."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-796f45a52ffa07aa91bbe739a0f9329d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RANDOM SEARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Random Search is the method individual bees use to find food sources when the dance language is not available."|</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-608651f2b4f999718f7ad6d8a9416dc0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A new hive is a structure where bees are introduced and begin their colony, managed by beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMOKE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Smoke is used to calm bees before handling the hive, helping to prevent stings and disturbances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A veil is a protective covering worn by beekeepers to shield their faces from bees, reducing the risk of stings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A new colony refers to a group of bees that have just started living in a new hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRITICAL TIME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Critical time refers to a period when the colony's survival is at risk, requiring immediate attention."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMALL YARD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A small yard is a limited space where the hive might be placed due to size constraints."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARGER PROPERTY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A larger property is a broader area where the hive might be placed, possibly with restrictions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDER CONTAINER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A feeder container is a specific type of feeder designed to hold food for the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INSECT REPELLENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Insect repellent is a tool used to protect the beekeeper from stings during hive management."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRITICAL TIME IN THE LIFE OF YOUR NEW COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Critical time in the life of your new colony refers to a period when the colony's survival is at risk, requiring immediate attention."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1c6642003e1962771aafdc3360a347d3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIRST HIVE BODY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"First Hive Body is the initial section of the hive containing frames that are being used and occupied by the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECOND HIVE BODY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Second Hive Body is the additional section of the hive added later to provide more space for the expanding colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter is the season when bees require stored resources for survival, necessitating adequate comb preparation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MONTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Month refers to the timeframe during which the bees have been feeding and expanding the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRAMES OF FOUNDATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Frames of Foundation are pre-made structures placed in the hive bodies to guide the bees in drawing out comb."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cover is a protective layer placed on top of the hive bodies to shield the bees and their comb from the elements."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OUTER FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Outer Frames are the frames located at the edges of the hive bodies, often less used by the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 92}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INNER FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inner Frames are the frames located in the middle of the hive bodies, typically more used by the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Season refers to the time of year, specifically mentioning Winter as a critical period for the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERFERENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Interference is the act of manually moving frames to ensure proper use and distribution of space within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 90}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNDERUSED FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Underused Frames are frames in the hive bodies that are not being actively used by the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 90}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPER USE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Proper Use refers to the optimal utilization of hive frames by the bees for comb drawing and resource storage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRAWING OUT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drawing Out is the process by which bees construct comb in the frames."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OCCUPIED FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Occupied Frames are frames in the hive bodies that contain comb or are being actively used by the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58e222836a11d1f2b7225f57ea3fe864</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BOARDMAN FEEDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Boardman feeder is a type of bee feeder that can attract stray bees if not properly buffered due to its location outside the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 91}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLAN SUPPLEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Plan Supplement is part of a restructuring plan and needs to be reviewed by the Supporting Lenders before filing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 31}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEED&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feed is a source of sustenance for the colony, currently less relied upon but still necessary."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPILLAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Spillage refers to the leakage of syrup from the feeder, which can attract bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEAKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Leaks refer to the dripping of syrup from the feeder, which can attract bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENTRANCE REDUCER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An entrance reducer is a tool used to reduce the size of the hive entrance, making it harder for bees to access the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STRAY BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stray bees are bees that are not part of the colony and may be attracted to the feeder."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-01a7b92c0bded7877f99a6813c111de0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
