<node id="&quot;PERFORMER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Performer is someone whose job is to convey heightened emotions to an audience through vocal production, physical gestures, and facial expressions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AUDIENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An Audience is the group of people who pay to experience a performance and are emotionally engaged by the performer."&lt;SEP&gt;"Audience is the group of people who pay to experience a vocal performance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Production is the act of producing sound through the voice to convey emotions and messages."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHYSICAL GESTURES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Physical Gestures are movements made by the body to enhance the emotional expression of a performer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FACIAL EXPRESSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Facial Expression is the use of facial muscles to convey emotions and reactions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MPA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"MPA is defined on a continuum with anxiety levels ranging from low to high and comprises four distinct components: affect, cognition, behavior, and physiology."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Performance Anxiety is a form of MPA that affects vocal athletes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Performance Anxiety is a form of MPA."&lt;SEP&gt;"Performance Anxiety is a heightened state of emotion experienced by performers, especially elite performers, before and during performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AFFECT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Affect in MPA includes feelings such as doom, panic, and anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COGNITION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cognition in MPA involves altered levels of concentration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEHAVIOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Behavior in MPA includes postural shifts, quivering, and trembling."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHYSIOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Physiology in MPA involves activation of the ANS system, resulting in the 'fight or flight' response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENALINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenaline is released by the brain in response to fear stimuli, causing physical changes such as increased heart rate, increased respiration, shaking, pale skin, dilated pupils, slowed digestion, bladder relaxation, dry mouth, and dry eyes, all of which severely affect vocal performance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline is released by the brain in response to fear stimuli, causing physical changes such as increased heart rate, increased respiration, shaking, pale skin, dilated pupils, slowed digestion, bladder relaxation, dry mouth, and dry eyes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL PERFORMANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Performance is affected by the physical changes caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal Performance is the act of conveying emotions and experiences to an audience through vocal production, physical gestures, and facial expressions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELITE PERFORMANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elite Performance is a highly skilled and emotionally intense vocal performance, often accompanied by performance anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMOTIONAL CONVEYANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Emotional Conveyance is the act of expressing emotions through vocal production, physical gestures, and facial expressions to an audience."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERNAL TURMOIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Internal Turmoil is the emotional and mental stress experienced by a singer in preparation for an elite performance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LITERATURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Literature is a source of documented information about performance anxiety and its components."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPAHN ET AL.&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Spahn et al. are researchers who have documented the four distinct components of MPA."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEUROLOGICAL PATHWAYS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Neurological Pathways are the two distinct pathways through which MPA is experienced, one quick and unconscious, the other involving conscious thought."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEAR STIMULI&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fear Stimuli are the triggers that cause the release of adrenaline and subsequent physical responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIFE-THREATENING SITUATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Life-Threatening Situation is a scenario that would trigger the 'fight or flight' response, similar to the one experienced during MPA."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEART RATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Heart Rate is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESPIRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Respiration is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SHAKING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Shaking is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."&lt;SEP&gt;"Shaking is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PALE SKIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pale Skin is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pale Skin is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DILATED PUPILS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dilated Pupils is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."&lt;SEP&gt;"Dilated Pupils is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SLOWED DIGESTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Slowed Digestion is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."&lt;SEP&gt;"Slowed Digestion is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLADDER RELAXATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bladder Relaxation is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bladder Relaxation is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRY MOUTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dry Mouth is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."&lt;SEP&gt;"Dry Mouth is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRY EYES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dry Eyes is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during MPA."&lt;SEP&gt;"Dry Eyes is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENALINE RELEASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenaline Release affects Vocal Performance by causing physical changes that can impair vocal function."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Bladder Relaxation as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Dilated Pupils as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Dry Eyes as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Dry Mouth as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Increased Heart Rate as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Increased Respiration as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Pale Skin as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Shaking as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release causes Slowed Digestion as a physical change during a fear or stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenaline Release is a physiological event triggered by fear or stress, resulting in various physical changes such as increased heart rate and respiration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INCREASED HEART RATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Increased Heart Rate is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INCREASED RESPIRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Increased Respiration is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during a fear or stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEAR/THREAT IDENTIFICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fear/Threat Identification is a conscious process that results in a slower physiologic response to a perceived threat."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fear/Threat Identification results in a slower physiologic response to a perceived threat."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PSYCHO-BEHAVIORAL THERAPY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
