  <data key="d2">chunk-98146bc44ee4d6b982895f8ab196757a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WELLNESS: INJURY PREVENTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wellness: Injury Prevention is a topic focused on preventing vocal injuries and understanding vocal wellness in singers, emphasizing the importance of general knowledge on common causes of voice disorders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7f6dfd6cf19346b800ac411171835010</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL INJURY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Injury refers to any harm or disorder affecting the vocal folds or related structures, often caused by abusive or misused vocal behaviors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7f6dfd6cf19346b800ac411171835010</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHONOTRAUMATIC BEHAVIORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Phonotraumatic Behaviors include actions such as yelling, screaming, loud talking, talking over noise, throat clearing, coughing, harsh sneezing, and boisterous laughing, which can lead to vocal injury."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7f6dfd6cf19346b800ac411171835010</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHRONIC VOCAL PROPERTIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chronic Vocal Properties refer to long-term vocal characteristics that can negatively impact vocal function, such as poor breathing techniques and inappropriate phonatory habits during conversational speech."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7f6dfd6cf19346b800ac411171835010</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICALLY RELATED ETIOLOGIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Medically Related Etiologies include various medical conditions that can impact vocal function, such as untreated chronic allergies, sinusitis, endocrine dysfunction, and hormonal imbalance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7f6dfd6cf19346b800ac411171835010</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;YELLING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Yelling is a phonotraumatic behavior that can cause vocal injury and is listed as a common cause of voice disorders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7f6dfd6cf19346b800ac411171835010</data>
</node>
