<edge source="&quot;DRUKER&quot;" target="&quot;CML PATIENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Druker administered the drug to CML patients, monitoring its effects and side effects."&lt;SEP&gt;"Druker is conducting a drug trial on CML patients, monitoring their disease progression and side effects."&lt;SEP&gt;"Druker, through his advocacy and testing, aimed to improve the prognosis for CML patients."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0be263d5a314742e36ec24dcf6eba279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DRUKER&quot;" target="&quot;PHYSICIANS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Druker is a member of the group of physicians conducting the drug trial."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CML PATIENTS&quot;" target="&quot;WHITE CELL COUNT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The white cell count is a critical indicator of the health status of CML patients, showing normal and elevated levels."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CML PATIENTS&quot;" target="&quot;GENETIC 'BRAKES'&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The concept of genetic 'brakes' is relevant to understanding the disease state of CML patients, particularly in terms of uncontrolled cell growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CML PATIENTS&quot;" target="&quot;PHYSICIANS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Physicians are administering the drug to CML patients, indicating a direct interaction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CML PATIENTS&quot;" target="&quot;DRUG&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The drug is being tested on CML patients to monitor its effects on their disease and side effects."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;GENETIC 'BRAKES'&quot;" target="&quot;RETINOBLASTOMA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Retinoblastoma provides insight into the genetic 'brakes' that can be lost, contributing to the development of cancer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;GENETIC 'BRAKES'&quot;" target="&quot;UNCONTROLLED GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The loss of genetic 'brakes' can lead to uncontrolled growth, a key feature of cancer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RETINOBLASTOMA&quot;" target="&quot;CHROMOSOME 13&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chromosome 13 is associated with genetic deletions in retinoblastoma cases, indicating its role in the genetic basis of the disease."&lt;SEP&gt;"Retinoblastoma is associated with deletions in a portion of both copies of chromosome 13, indicating the importance of this chromosomal region in the disease's development."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RETINOBLASTOMA&quot;" target="&quot;TUMOR SUPPRESSOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The retinoblastoma gene is a tumor suppressor that, when lost or altered, can lead to the development of retinoblastoma, highlighting its role in preventing tumor formation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RETINOBLASTOMA&quot;" target="&quot;CELL CYCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The retinoblastoma gene controls a critical decision in the cell cycle, and its loss or alteration can disrupt this process, leading to the development of retinoblastoma."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RETINOBLASTOMA&quot;" target="&quot;CELL DIVISION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The retinoblastoma gene plays a role in controlling cell division, and its loss or alteration can lead to uncontrolled cell division, contributing to the development of retinoblastoma."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RETINOBLASTOMA&quot;" target="&quot;DNA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The retinoblastoma gene is involved in the regulation of DNA replication and cell division, and its loss or alteration can affect these processes, leading to the development of retinoblastoma."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ACCELERATOR&quot;" target="&quot;UNCONTROLLED GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The concept of an accelerator being stuck is used to describe uncontrolled growth in cancer cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BRAKE LINES&quot;" target="&quot;UNCONTROLLED GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Brake lines represent the mechanisms that prevent uncontrolled growth, which can be lost in cancer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR SUPPRESSORS&quot;" target="&quot;UNCONTROLLED GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Tumor suppressors act as brakes to prevent uncontrolled growth, which is a hallmark of cancer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR SUPPRESSORS&quot;" target="&quot;GENETIC DELETIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Genetic deletions can lead to the loss of tumor suppressors, contributing to uncontrolled cell growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a68ae106dd6ea1a8a7115307e710fd4a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;PROTO-ONCOGENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Oncogenes and proto-oncogenes are related in that proto-oncogenes can become oncogenes when mutated, often requiring only one copy to be altered for cancer formation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;_BCR_ / _ABL_&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The _bcr_ / _abl_ gene is an example of an oncogene, where the alteration of one copy of the gene can lead to cancer formation, contrasting with the retinoblastoma gene which requires both copies to be altered."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR SUPPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;RB GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">40.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Rb gene functions as a tumor suppressor, controlling cell division and preventing tumor formation, which is disrupted in retinoblastoma."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cbd375334f702a84e935d6ce2515fdd4</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CANCER&quot;" target="&quot;RB&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inactivation or loss of the Rb gene leads to cancer by allowing for constitutive cell growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CANCER&quot;" target="&quot;MONOD AND JACOB'S SPECULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Monod and Jacob's speculation about cancer resulting from the inactivation of a repressor of cell multiplication aligns with the role of the Rb gene in cancer development."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CANCER&quot;" target="&quot;LOGICAL THERAPY AND RATIONAL DRUGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Logical therapy and rational drugs aim to target specific genetic mutations, such as the inactivation of the Rb gene, to treat cancer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CANCER&quot;" target="&quot;SURGERY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Surgery is a method used to treat cancer, often involving the removal of tumors or affected tissues."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CANCER&quot;" target="&quot;IRRADIATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Irradiation is another method used to treat cancer, involving the use of high-energy radiation to kill cancer cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CANCER&quot;" target="&quot;COCKTAILS OF DRUGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cocktails of drugs are a combination of medications used to treat cancer, targeting dividing cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CELL MULTIPLICATION&quot;" target="&quot;RB&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Rb gene represses cell multiplication, and its inactivation or loss allows for uncontrolled cell growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-32b2a5cf3b4f7ee70356b1bcc75677b8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
