  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Bankruptcy Code provides the legal framework for the Chapter 11 Case, specifically mentioning Sections 503(b)(1)(A) and 507(a)(2)."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a084f2e9cb7d42ed40a5f082d5224a62</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHAPTER 11 CASE&quot;" target="&quot;SECTIONS 503(B)(1)(A)&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sections 503(b)(1)(A) of the Bankruptcy Code will treat the Expense Reimbursement Amount as administrative expenses in the Chapter 11 Case."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a084f2e9cb7d42ed40a5f082d5224a62</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHAPTER 11 CASE&quot;" target="&quot;SECTIONS 507(A)(2)&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sections 507(a)(2) of the Bankruptcy Code will also treat the Expense Reimbursement Amount as administrative expenses in the Chapter 11 Case."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a084f2e9cb7d42ed40a5f082d5224a62</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;STINGING&quot;" target="&quot;NOSE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Stinging is a defensive action triggered by the nose, which can be perceived as an aggressive action by a bee."</data>
