</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;INHIBITOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Inhibitors bind to enzymes at sites other than the active site, altering their shape and function."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-95d378a4a5d837b5df62cf1349844f34</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;SYRUP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The presence of syrup in the feeder induces the production of enzymes in bacteria, which helps in breaking down the syrup."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bacteria produce enzymes in response to the presence of lactose, which is a component of the syrup provided in the feeder."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;INDUCER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inducer, which is a type of sugar, triggers the production of enzymes in bacteria, allowing them to break down lactose."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;INSPECTION PROCEDURE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inspection procedure ensures that the bees have a consistent food supply, which is necessary for the production of enzymes by bacteria."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;ENZYME PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Enzyme production is the process by which bacteria produce enzymes in response to the presence of lactose and the inducer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
