<edge source="&quot;REGULATION OF ENZYME PRODUCTION&quot;" target="&quot;OBSERVATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The simple observation that bacteria make enzymes in the presence of the inducer was a key part of Monod's research."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIAL COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;ENZYME SYNTHESIS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A bacterial colony is the environment where bacteria live and produce enzymes in response to the presence of lactose and the inducer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME SYNTHESIS&quot;" target="&quot;SUGAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inducer, which is sugar, triggers the production of enzymes in bacteria, allowing them to break down lactose."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a10e4014c4f193eee14a336747f04aa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME SYNTHESIS&quot;" target="&quot;REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Regulation controls the process of enzyme synthesis, which is the core of Monod's research."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-babaf934dcb765f08d028d1b33488eef</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME SYNTHESIS&quot;" target="&quot;BREAKDOWN SUGAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Breakdown Sugar is broken down by the β-galactosidase enzyme, which is part of the regulatory mechanism."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-babaf934dcb765f08d028d1b33488eef</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
