  <data key="d6">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FEAR&quot;" target="&quot;EMOTIONAL REACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Fear is a natural reaction to a stressful situation and is discussed in relation to emotional excitation and perceived threat."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMER&quot;" target="&quot;AUDIENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Performer conveys heightened emotions to an Audience through vocal production, physical gestures, and facial expressions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMER&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vocal Production is the act of producing sound through the voice to convey emotions and messages by a Performer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMER&quot;" target="&quot;PHYSICAL GESTURES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Physical Gestures are movements made by the body to enhance the emotional expression of a Performer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMER&quot;" target="&quot;FACIAL EXPRESSION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Facial Expression is the use of facial muscles to convey emotions and reactions by a Performer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d4eddd6f56e7059a2cea2cbd8f99d57a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;AUDIENCE&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL PERFORMANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Audience pays to experience Vocal Performances, which can be emotionally intense and anxiety-inducing."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;AFFECT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Performance Anxiety includes affective components such as feelings of doom, panic, and anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;COGNITION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Performance Anxiety affects cognitive processes, leading to altered levels of concentration."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;BEHAVIOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Performance Anxiety manifests in behavioral changes such as postural shifts, quivering, and trembling."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;PHYSIOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Performance Anxiety triggers physiological responses, including activation of the ANS system and the 'fight or flight' response."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL PERFORMANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vocal Performance is often accompanied by Performance Anxiety, especially in elite performances."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;ELITE PERFORMANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Elite Performance is characterized by high levels of Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;EMOTIONAL CONVEYANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Performance Anxiety can affect the quality of Emotional Conveyance during a performance."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;INTERNAL TURMOIL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Performance Anxiety is closely linked to Internal Turmoil, which singers experience before elite performances."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;LITERATURE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Literature documents the components of Performance Anxiety, including Affect, Cognition, Behavior, and Physiology."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;SPAHN ET AL.&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Spahn et al. have researched and documented the components of Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;NEUROLOGICAL PATHWAYS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Neurological Pathways explain how Performance Anxiety is experienced, both quickly and consciously."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;FEAR STIMULI&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Fear Stimuli trigger the release of adrenaline, leading to the physical changes associated with Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;LIFE-THREATENING SITUATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Life-Threatening Situation is a metaphorical comparison to the intensity of Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;HEART RATE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Heart Rate is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;RESPIRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Respiration is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;SHAKING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Shaking is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;PALE SKIN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pale Skin is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;DILATED PUPILS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dilated Pupils is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;SLOWED DIGESTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Slowed Digestion is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;BLADDER RELAXATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bladder Relaxation is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;DRY MOUTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dry Mouth is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERFORMANCE ANXIETY&quot;" target="&quot;DRY EYES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dry Eyes is a physical change caused by the release of adrenaline during Performance Anxiety."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHYSIOLOGY&quot;" target="&quot;ADRENALINE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Adrenaline is part of the physiological response to fear stimuli, causing physical changes that affect vocal performance."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cb08e38144366f1bcb1f92e17c2050fa</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
